@prefix : <https://w3id.org/ontology/dlr#> .
@prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix xml: <http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix time: <http://www.w3.org/2006/time#> .
@base <https://w3id.org/ontology/dlr#> .


###################################################################################################################################################################
# Description:
#------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# This example includes a deontic statement (1) and a factual statement (2). The latter complies with the former, and this is correctly inferred.
# - (1) "John is obliged to pay the rent"
# - (2) "John pays the rent by card at 3:15 pm"
# It is inferred that (2) complies with (1).
# Note that no time frame is specified for the obligation. Therefore, it is interpreted as John being obliged to pay the rent "at some time", meaning that 
# any time is acceptable for compliance. In a real-world scenario, however, there would either be an explicit deadline, or John would be required to pay 
# the rent "within a reasonable time". The notion of "reasonable" is subject to legal interpretation and is beyond the scope of this paper.
###################################################################################################################################################################

###################################################################################################################################################################
# Input facts:
###################################################################################################################################################################

#John is obliged to pay his rent.
:epjo rdf:type :A-Obligatory, :Pay; :has-agent :John; :has-object :rent. :rent :rent-of :John.

#John pays his rent by card at 3.15pm (of 1/1/2025, UTC time zone)
:epj rdf:type :Rexist, :Pay; :has-agent :John; :has-object :rent; :has-instrument :card; :has-time [time:inXSDDateTime "2025-01-01T15:15:00Z"^^xsd:dateTime].

